text: The Spartakiad (or Spartakiade) was an international sports event from 1928 to 1937. Spartakiad may also refer to: * Spartakiad of Peoples of the USSR, mass multi-event competitions in the Soviet Union from 1956 to 1991 * Spartakiad (Albania), multi-event competitions in Albania from 1959 to 1989 * Spartakiad (Czechoslovakia), mass gymnastics events in Czechoslovakia from 1955 to 1990
title: Spartakiad (disambiguation)
